    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Painting style from the Heian period (794-1185) that may have referred specifically to the work of professional painters of the imperial court and was notable for its ink-line drawing and action packed scenes. This style, considered masculine, was sometimes contrasted with "onna-e," feminine painting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
